54 template <typename T, typename U>
55 class CCreateMap {
56 private:
57  std::map<T, U> m_map;
58 public:
59  CCreateMap(const T& key, const U& val) {
60  m_map[key] = val;
61  }
62  CCreateMap<T, U>& operator()(const T& key, const U& val) {
63  m_map[key] = val;
64  return *this;
65  }
66  operator std::map<T, U>() {
67  return m_map;
68  }
69 };

3165  // Cannot have ; at the beginning or the end

3171  }

3175  newstring.append(": may not have ending semicolon");
3176  return newstring;
3177  }
3178 
3179 
3180  // use the ";" token to determine the number of design variables
3181  // This works because semicolon is not one of the delimiters in tokenize string
3182  this->nFFD = 0;
3183  for (unsigned int i = 0; i < static_cast<unsigned int>(option_value.size()); i++) {
3184  if (option_value[i].compare(";") == 0) {
3185  this->nFFD++;
3186  }
3187  }
3188 
3189  // One more design variable than semicolon
3190  this->nFFD++;
3191

3193  for (unsigned short iFFD = 0; iFFD < this->nFFD; iFFD++) {

3199  unsigned int i = 0;
3200

3202 
3203  nDegreeFFD = 3;
3204 
3205  for (unsigned short iDegreeFFD = 0; iDegreeFFD < nDegreeFFD; iDegreeFFD++) {

3207  ss >> this->DegreeFFD[iFFD][iDegreeFFD];
3208  i++;
3209  }
3210

3215  newstring.append(": a FFD degree in the configuration file has the wrong number of parameters");
3216  return newstring;
3217  }
3218  i++;
3219  }
3220 
3221  }
3222 
3223  // Need to return something...

3225  }
